data.description: This charming home, built in 1869, is located in the heart of downtown Evansville. 208 Oak, part of the Mursinna-Schultze double house welcomes you with 3 bedrooms and 2.5 bathrooms and offers a perfect blend of classic architecture and modern comfort. The exterior boasts a traditional design with many windows and a welcoming front porch.  Inside, you'll find a spacious living area, a well-appointed kitchen, and a formal dining room. The three bedrooms provide ample space for a family or guests, and the 2.5 bathrooms ensure convenience. Hardwood floors and beautiful fireplaces showcase the home's historical character, while modern updates offer a comfortable living experience. A well-maintained backyard and a prime downtown location make this property an ideal blend of historic charm and city living convenience.
